gomodel:SYNGO_5105  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: DHHC2 (ZDHHC2) antibody was validated by siRNA DHHC2-knockdown and westernblots. DHHC2 and PSD95 (DLG4) were enriched in PSD biochemical fractions. Confocal imaging showed DHHC2 localized to dendritic puncta and the cell body.\n\nFigure 6: TIRFM imaging revealed that more DHHC2 was recruited near the membrane upon Kyn or TTX treatment (Fig. 6, B and C; and Video 4), where PSD-95 localized (Fig. S4 A). This translocation was activity sensitive as it was reversible upon washing out of Kyn (Fig. 6 D). Furthermore, we found that Kyn or TTX steadily induced colocalization of endogenous DHHC2 with PSD-95 over 48 h (Fig. 6, E and F).\n\nFigure 7: Activity-sensitive PSD-95 palmitoylation by DHHC2 is necessary for homeostatic increase of AMPARs.. Experimental description: protein sequence validation;\n\"Cloning and plasmid constructions - The rat cDNAs of ... DHHC2 (GenBank/EMBL/DDBJ accession no. AF228917)\"\nGenBank AF228917 --> GenBank AAF43032 --> uniprot BLAST confirms this is accession Q9JKR5 (ZDHC2_RAT)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5105" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

